HEADWORD: Agriculturist
<hw>Ag`ri*cul"tur*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One engaged or skilled in
agriculture; a husbandman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The farmer is always a practitioner, the <qex>agriculturist</qex>
may be a mere theorist.</q> <rj><qau>Crabb.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Agrief</ent>⟦br⟧
